This paper focuses on the analysis of software packaging ecosystems, which involves software engineering practices such as dependency management, versioning, and package release. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely sub-category. cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely, as the paper discusses package managers for different programming languages. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible sub-category, as the paper analyzes the network structure of package dependencies. cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are less likely but still possible, as the paper proposes novel metrics to capture different aspects of package dependency networks, which could be seen as a form of data analysis.
